# Configuration Change Instructions:
# ===================================
#
# Blue-Green Traffic Switching:
# -----------------------------
# To switch traffic from blue to green:
# 1. Update the upstream togather_backend server directive:
#    FROM: server togather-server-blue:8080;
#    TO:   server togather-server-green:8080;
# 2. Test configuration: docker compose -f docker-compose.blue-green.yml exec nginx nginx -t
# 3. Reload nginx: docker compose -f docker-compose.blue-green.yml exec nginx nginx -s reload
# 4. Verify: curl -I http://localhost/health (check X-Togather-Slot header)
#
# To switch traffic from green to blue:
# 1. Update the upstream togather_backend server directive:
#    FROM: server togather-server-green:8080;
#    TO:   server togather-server-blue:8080;
# 2. Test configuration: docker compose -f docker-compose.blue-green.yml exec nginx nginx -t
# 3. Reload nginx: docker compose -f docker-compose.blue-green.yml exec nginx nginx -s reload
# 4. Verify: curl -I http://localhost/health (check X-Togather-Slot header)
#
# Deployment Script (T021) will automate this process with safety checks.
#
# TLS/SSL Configuration for Production:
# -------------------------------------
# 1. Obtain SSL certificates (recommended: Let's Encrypt via certbot)
# 2. Uncomment the HTTPS server block (lines ~200-350)
# 3. Update ssl_certificate and ssl_certificate_key paths
# 4. Update server_name to match your domain
# 5. Uncomment the HTTP-to-HTTPS redirect in the HTTP server block
# 6. Test: nginx -t
# 7. Reload: nginx -s reload
#
# Rate Limiting Configuration:
# ---------------------------
# Current limits (adjustable via limit_req_zone directives):
# - General API: 30 requests/minute per IP (burst: 10)
# - Batch ingestion: 10 requests/minute per IP (burst: 3)
# - Auth endpoints: 5 requests/minute per IP (burst: 2)
# - Health/metrics: No rate limiting
#
# To adjust limits, modify the limit_req_zone directives in the http block.
# Format: rate=NUMr/m (per minute) or rate=NUMr/s (per second)
#
# Security Headers:
# ----------------
# The configuration includes comprehensive security headers:
# - X-Frame-Options: Prevents clickjacking
# - X-Content-Type-Options: Prevents MIME sniffing
# - X-XSS-Protection: Enables XSS filter
# - Content-Security-Policy: Controls resource loading
# - Strict-Transport-Security: Forces HTTPS (when TLS enabled)
# - Permissions-Policy: Controls browser features
#
# Adjust Content-Security-Policy based on your application's needs.

